---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="How It Works — llm-contract"
  description="Understand the llm-contract acceptance boundary: instructions, clean, verify, classify, repair, retry."
>
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold text-white mb-4 tracking-tight"><span class="gradient-text">How It Works</span></h1>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 text-lg max-w-3xl">
      The model is probabilistic. The acceptance boundary is deterministic.
      <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-surface px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm border border-border">llm-contract</code> treats model output as untrusted input until it passes runtime checks.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-14 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6 tracking-tight">Contract loop</h2>
    <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6 max-w-3xl">
      <div class="font-mono text-sm space-y-2 text-zinc-300">
        <div>LLM output</div>
        <div class="text-zinc-600">↓</div>
        <div><span class="text-accent">instructions(schema)</span> — generate deterministic system instructions</div>
        <div class="text-zinc-600">↓</div>
        <div><span class="text-accent">clean()</span> — extract and normalize JSON</div>
        <div class="text-zinc-600">↓</div>
        <div><span class="text-accent">verify(schema + invariants)</span> — validate shape and domain rules</div>
        <div class="text-zinc-600">↓</div>
        <div><span class="text-accent">classify failure</span> — identify what went wrong</div>
        <div class="text-zinc-600">↓</div>
        <div><span class="text-accent">generate repair</span> — return targeted feedback</div>
        <div class="text-zinc-600">↓</div>
        <div><span class="text-accent">retry within policy</span> — bounded attempts</div>
        <div class="text-zinc-600">↓</div>
        <div><span class="text-emerald-400">typed result</span> or <span class="text-red-400">explicit failure</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-14 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6 tracking-tight">What each step gives you</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5 card-hover"><p class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">clean()</p><p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Handles markdown fences, prose wrapping, and value coercion before validation.</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5 card-hover"><p class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">verify(schema + invariants)</p><p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Applies structural and domain rules. Nothing passes unless both layers pass.</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5 card-hover"><p class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">classify + repair</p><p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Transforms failure into explicit categories and targeted correction messages.</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5 card-hover"><p class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">retry policy</p><p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Retries are bounded and configurable, with optional linear/exponential backoff.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
